text: Zdeněk Remsa (29 December 1928 – 22 June 2019) was a Czechoslovak ski jumper. He was born in Horní Branná. He competed at the 1948 Winter Olympics in St. Moritz. Remsa died on 22 June 2019, at the age of 90. ==References== ==Other websites== *Zdeněk Remsa at the International Olympic Committee Category:1928 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Olympians for Czechoslovakia Category:Skiers
